column5: Seems it has been since the first week of May since I wet a line. Extreme cabin fever is in full swing.  Am I the only one.
Yep....No cabin fever here....I have a full spring/summer of outings planned and to round it out a nice 4 days of hunting Muskie with Thorpe in October!
Yep...for May, I think I shore fished almost every day.
i was out today and had a rather succesful day get out there and catch some fish i got a report coming along later tonight or tomorow
Can't wait.  Every little bit counts.

Went out 5 minutes from hear and shore fished the N Sask River.  Not a bite but shot the hoot with a boat that came in where I was shore fishing and the locals  said they caught 15  pickeral and one sturgeon.  Showed me a pic of a 30 lb,  At least I have hope.  Just moved hear last Aug testing the waters.
well at least some of you are out and about............
